[thinking] I’m considering using the fully qualified @org.junit.Test for nested tests, which sidesteps the need for vintage dependency discovery. Since all tests are currently using Jupiter, it seems safer to stick with that for the top-level tests. Invoking JUnitCore for the nested tests works well, too. If vintage isn't available, the top-level tests should still run. I’ll modify the imports to reflect this change and resolve any name collisions. It’s a solid plan to reduce risk!
