er might not support non-public inner classes, but it seems like mine is public static, which is good. I need to remember to create or update tests only under the source root and update support files in the target test project only when new tests require it. The build file looks fine, and I think I don't need any metadata edits since I already had the native resource, though the reporter only indicates low coverage without specifics.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OISY1uIXCebXLuTiIocsfHQP|fc_023f6ddaa1494552016a2ab7f17da48196aef4576ef6eca1e0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/RunnerProviderTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2094, "output": 927, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30157, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781184475498, "responseId": "resp_023f6ddaa1494552016a2ab7dc0e3481969d7efc7bfa55ee71"}}
